  "sections": [
    {
      "name": "Ogre Boss",
      "sources": [
        {
          "errata": {
            "alt": "1.1",
            "aonid": 221,
            "game-obj": "Sources",
            "name": "1.1",
            "type": "link"
          },
          "link": {
            "alt": "Monster Core pg. 251",
            "aonid": 221,
            "game-obj": "Sources",
            "name": "Monster Core pg. 251",
            "type": "link"
          },
          "name": "Monster Core",
          "page": 251,
          "type": "source"
        }
      ],
      "text": "In ogre society, might makes more than right\u2014it makes the rules. The strongest or most violent ogre in a family (in most cases, this is the same ogre) is invariably that family's boss. Quick to hook fallen foes on their weapons, even other ogres fear the repercussions of displeasing an ogre boss. When an ogre boss barks out commands, the other members of the family move quickly to obey.",
      "type": "section"
    }
  ],
  "sources": [
